<section xml:id="C14.S6">
<title>Integer Order</title>           
<subsection xml:id="C14.S6.SS1">
<title>Nonnegative Integer Orders</title>         
<para xml:id="C14.S6.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C14.S6.SS1.p1.s1">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S6.SS1.p1.m1">m=0,1,2,\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.6.1" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E1">\mathsf{P}^{m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=(-1)^{m}\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{m/2}\frac{{ \mathrm{d}}^{m}\mathsf{P}_{\nu}\left(x\right)}{{\mathrm{d}x}^{m}},</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.6.2" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E2">\mathsf{Q}^{m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=(-1)^{m}\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{m/2}\frac{{ \mathrm{d}}^{m}\mathsf{Q}_{\nu}\left(x\right)}{{\mathrm{d}x}^{m}}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C14.S6.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.6.3" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E3">P^{m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left(x^{2}-1\right)^{m/2}\frac{{\mathrm{d}}^{m}P_{ \nu}\left(x\right)}{{\mathrm{d}x}^{m}},</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.6.4" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E4">Q^{m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left(x^{2}-1\right)^{m/2}\frac{{\mathrm{d}}^{m}Q_{ \nu}\left(x\right)}{{\mathrm{d}x}^{m}},</Math> <Math equation-number="14.6.5" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E5">{\left(\nu+1\right)_{m}}\boldsymbol{Q}^{m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=(-1)^{m}\left(x ^{2}-1\right)^{m/2}\frac{{\mathrm{d}}^{m}\boldsymbol{Q}_{\nu}\left(x\right)}{{ \mathrm{d}x}^{m}}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C14.S6.SS2">
<title>Negative Integer Orders</title>         
<para xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p1.s1">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p1.m1">m=1,2,3,\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="14.6.6" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E6">\mathsf{P}^{-m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left(1-x^{2}\right)^{-m/2}\int_{x}^{1}\! \dots\!\int_{x}^{1}P_{\nu}\left(x\right)\left(\!\mathrm{d}x\right)^{m}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="14.6.7" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E7">P^{-m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=\left(x^{2}-1\right)^{-m/2}\int_{1}^{x}\!\dots\! \int_{1}^{x}P_{\nu}\left(x\right)\left(\!\mathrm{d}x\right)^{m}</Math> ,, <Math equation-number="14.6.8" mode="display" xml:id="C14.S6.E8">Q^{-m}_{\nu}\left(x\right)=(-1)^{m}\left(x^{2}-1\right)^{-m/2}\*\int_{x}^{ \infty}\!\dots\!\int_{x}^{\infty}Q_{\nu}\left(x\right)\left(\!\mathrm{d}x \right)^{m}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C14.S6.SS2.p2.s1">
For connections between positive and negative integer orders see (14.9.3), (14.9.4), and (14.9.13).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
</section>
